# Plugin Development Rules (2025)

**Modern Plugin Development Guidelines:**
- Use TypeScript 5.4+ with strict type checking enabled
- Follow modern ES2024+ syntax and features (top-level await, pipeline operator, etc.)
- Use modern bundlers like Vite, esbuild, or Rollup for plugin builds
- Implement proper tree-shaking and code splitting
- Use modern testing frameworks (Vitest, Playwright, or Jest with modern configs)
- Follow modern security practices (content security policies, input validation)
- Use modern error handling with structured error objects
- Implement proper logging with structured logging (Pino, Winston, or similar)
- Use modern dependency management with proper versioning
- Follow modern CI/CD practices with automated testing and deployment
- Use modern monitoring and observability (OpenTelemetry, structured metrics)
- Implement proper TypeScript decorators and metadata
- Use modern async patterns (async/await, Promise.allSettled, etc.)
- Follow modern performance practices (lazy loading, memoization, caching)
- Use modern state management patterns (Zustand, Jotai, or similar)
- Implement proper plugin lifecycle management
- Use modern validation libraries (Zod, Joi, or similar)
- Follow modern accessibility standards (WCAG 2.1 AA+)
- Use modern internationalization practices
- Implement proper plugin configuration with schema validation
